* bankruptcy
	* bankruptcies happening simultaneously is bad
		* bankruptcies happening simultaneously can increase their harm by multiple times; financial collapses can affect the real economy, and they strengthen each other's effects through real economic and financial relationships
	* the state should not incentivise debt
		* that leads to mass debt and hence occasionally mass bankruptcy
	* the state should not transfer responsibility
		# links-to internal cintjxjyjcopyarvn
* land ownership by foreigners should be allowed
	* the ultimate owner remains the state, which can easily even confiscate it
	* the exchange, because it is mutually voluntary, is good for both parties, including the domestic one
* countering negative externalities
	* the optimal method to decrease activities that hurt public good [for example the environment] is taxing
	* optimality is achieved by the prices being accurate
		# links-to internal gvztxekronaaqjyqn
	* such taxation is a correction of the prices by their external cost
	* an other greate advantage of it is the extra income for the state
